</p>
<p>And then found out that we <em>really</em> only want to add this to input fields.</p>
<p>How can we do that? I know that this is a <em>text</em> type. So maybe, instead of adding
the icon to <code>form_row</code>, we could override the <code>text_widget</code> block and add it there.
That would <em>only</em> affect text fields.</p>
<p>Go into <code>form_div_layout.html.twig</code> and look for <code>text_widget</code>. Woh! It's not here!
That means Symfony must be using <code>form_widget</code>. That block <em>does</em> exist:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="177f085fc6">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
