<h2 id="the-craziness-of-twig-in-form-themes">The Craziness of Twig in Form Themes <a class="headerlink" href="complex-blocks-parent-function#the-craziness-of-twig-in-form-themes" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Now, check out this logic: form theme templates will have some of the <em>craziest</em>
Twig code you'll ever see! In normal words, this says:</p>
<blockquote><p>If type is not defined or file does not equal type, add a new <code>form-control</code> class.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>To make this happen, it uses the <code>attr</code> variable that we were playing with before
and <em>merges</em> in the new class, adding a space in case there was already a class.</p>
<h2 id="stealing-parent-blocks-with-use">Stealing Parent Blocks with use <a class="headerlink" href="complex-blocks-parent-function#stealing-parent-blocks-with-use" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Before <em>we</em> make any changes, go back and refresh. Woh! It doesn't work - that's
surprising. The problem is this <code>parent()</code> call:</p>
