<p>We understand that in normal Twig templates, you can override parent blocks and use
the <code>parent()</code> function. But check this out: our template does <em>not</em> extend any Twig
template... and we don't want it to! For reasons that honestly aren't very important,
a form theme template should never extend anything.</p>
<p>But wait, then, how did this code work in the Bootstrap template? Go look: at the
top, it has a <code>use</code> for <code>form_div_layout.html.twig</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="770933a507">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
