<p>The <code>use</code> says:</p>
<blockquote><p>I don't <em>actually</em> want to extend this other template. But, please allow me
to call the parent() function as <em>if</em> I were extending it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The <code>use</code> statement is an awesome Twig feature that allows you to just, grab and
use random blocks from a different template. It's advanced, but now it's in your
toolkit! Go you!</p>
<p>At the top of our template, <code>use 'bootstrap_3_layout.html.twig'</code>:</p>
