<h2 id="the-error-icon-in-the-widget">The Error Icon in the Widget <a class="headerlink" href="complex-blocks-parent-function#the-error-icon-in-the-widget" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Finally, we can move the icon to this block. First, keep that <code>showErrorIcon</code> variable:
we need that to add the <code>has-feedback</code> class. But copy it and move it down into
<code>form_widget_simple</code>, inside the <code>if</code> statement... because, it turns out, we probably
also don't want to show the error icon if this is a file upload field:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="3be7dc97d0">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
